6:
Good morning, everyone. You've
come at a good time.
9:
I was wondering if there is anything
you need help with. My hands are
very free at the moment...
14:
I'm afraid we don't have any special
requests for today...
21:
What's wrong? Most people are
usually overjoyed to find out they
have a day off.
24:
Are they? I simply... am not familiar
with the concept, I suppose.
27:
Lyra, you're still young. Surely there
must be something out there that
you want to do?
33:
How about your music, Lyra? You're
an incredible performer! Surely you
like playing the violin?
38:
I... I must admit, I think playing the
violin is the only thing I really know
how to do.
39:
I don't know if it is something I can
say I "like". I merely had to do it in
order to survive...
42:
That reminds me. When we last saw
you fight, it seemed you were able
to use some sort of magic...
50:
It was given to me by my... former
patron. To protect myself while I
ventured through Kaleidoscope.
52:
I wouldn't be able to fight if I didn't
have it. If anything, every time I play
it I'm reminded of all the battles I've
fought. I'm not sure I can say I like
doing it.
57: Why not try playing a song you like?
61:
A singer once told me that is the
secret to having fun.
65:
I don't know if it will necessarily be
"fun", but I suppose there is a song
I'd like to play...
75: Huh? Is that really where it ends?
81:
I'm afraid that's all I can play, at
least at my current skill level.
82:
This violin is... very particular—if I go
even slightly off pitch, it is likely to do
something destructive.
84:
Something destructive? What do
you mean?
86:
One time, I played a wrong note in
the Kaleidoscope and caused an
entire room to collapse...
92:
If even someone as skilled as you
can't perform the whole thing, then...
That must be quite the song.
95:
To tell you the truth, I don't
remember where I first heard it. Still,
I practice this melody every single
day.
97:
I'd like to be able to play it to
completion one day. That's been my
dream for quite a long time.
101:
I suppose continuing to practice is
the only avenue left...
107:
There might be another way. We
could talk to the maker of the violin
directly.
109:
The instrument's design reminds me
of Dia's sound unit. It could be from
her world.
114:
Well! There's no doubt about
it—that's Carol. I can't believe you
found her!
117: Carol? My violin has a name?
120:
Yep. Musical performance support
unit Carol—my past self built this
one.
121:
Right, I should explain—that was
before the massive memory wipe
that occurred. I must have lost track
of her at that point, heh.
123:
So you're her partner, huh? Is she
impossible to deal with or what?
Haha.
127:
On the contrary, it's me who should
be ashamed that I can't manage to
master her.
132:
Can you tell us how to play this
violin without having it go on a
rampage?
135:
G-go on a rampage? What the heck
are you talking about?
138:
Wait a minute. Are you saying that
you didn't design this violin to be
able to fire off magic?
141:
Magic?! I have no idea what you're
talking about—I don't deal with
occult stuff like that, I just make
instruments!
144:
Hmm, it looks like this bit here was
installed after I made it.
147:
Someone altered the violin... But
who, exactly?
149:
I can't believe someone would go
and turn my violin into a weapon!
Well, I guess I kind of CAN believe it.
People will do anything.
152:
I'm terribly sorry. I've been using this
violin to fight battles all this time...
155:
Nah, don't sweat it. You're Carol's
partner now—I have a feeling you've
treated her well. I'm not holding any
grudges about this.
157:
But still, with this enhancement, it
won't have the same timbre it used
to before. That's a shame.
161:
Would... Would you mind if I
performed for you?
163:
This violin and I are very similar, I've
realized. We were both abandoned
and lost something very dear to us.
167:
Still... I promise I'll do my best to help
restore Carol to her original form.
173: She seems beaten up about this.
177:
I'm not sure if much can be done
about the violin. I just hope she can
overcome this.
189: I'm sorry, Carol. But also, thank you.
190:
Thank you for always helping me.
This time, it's my turn to be of use.
196:
This is that melody Lyra was talking
about before! From her memories.
199:
I see. Is this why you left, Carol? To
meet her?
203:
Well, that was a wonderful show! I
feel a burst of inspiration coming on
now!
205:
Thank you, Lyra. Your performance
with Carol was incredible.
208:
No, it's I who should be grateful.
Thank you for building Carol and
letting me perform with her.
212: So Lyra, did you have fun?
